<br>
They're actually pretty good pet weapons too, as they are both 1HP, and have a dmg/dly of 6/18 and 11/28, respectively.<br>
<br>
As already stated above though, the Gnoll Hide Lariat procs a stun, so that's the best for general dmg/aggro management, but I like to entertain myself and my party with those Tridents whenever possible - a frog in Guk with Tiny Pet cast on him is particularly amusing, as I did this to help a fellow chanter camp the AC a while back.  It's also a good way to quickly identify which one is your pet when the names are all the same, since Trickster's isn't an option anymore. /mourn Trickster's.<br>
<br>
